ASEAN, South Korea Consider Plan to Set Up Center 
The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and South Korea have
agreed to study a plan for an ASEAN promotion center in Seoul, Thai
Foreign Ministry said here today.
The ministry said in a statement that the center would promote the
culture and traditions of ASEAN members and provide information on
tourism.
The agreement was one of several reached during the second meeting in
Seoul recently.
The two sides expressed satisfaction with the expansion of cooperation
in trade and investment, and agreed to hold a seminar on investment
soon.
